n April 16, 2020. Unlike her previous records, its single release includes multiple versions of the song recorded in several languages as a [[duet]] featuring various recording artists \u2014 such as French singer [[Zaz (singer)|Zaz]], Canadian-Moroccan singer [[Faouzia]] for the Arabic version, Spanish singer [[Blas Cant\u00f3]], German musical duo [[Glasperlenspiel (duo)|Glasperlenspiel]], Israeli singer [[Maya Bouskilla]] for the Hebrew version, and the American [[Deaf West Theatre]] for the [[ASL]] version.\n\n== Composition and release ==\n\"I Dare You\" was written by [[Jesse Shatkin]] and [[Jeff Gitelman|Gitty]], [[Natalie Hemby]], Laura Veltz and [[Ben West (musician)|Ben West]].<ref>{{cite web |title=I Dare You to Love (Kelly Clarkson ver.) |url=https://www.warnerchappell.com/song-details/WW%20015349870%2000/dd46778e-a982-4232-c639-f16cd3a71ec6 |publisher=[[Warner Chappell Music]] |accessdate=April 2, 2020}}</ref> In her opening monologue on a February 2020 episode of her [[The Kelly Clarkson Show|self-titled talk show]], Clarkson revealed her plans to release the song.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wass |first1=Mike |title=Kelly Clarkson Is Releasing A New Single Called \"I Dare You\" |url=https://www.idolator.com/7907322/kelly-clarkson-is-releasing-a-new-single-called-i-dare-you |website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] |publisher=Hive Media |accessdate=April 2, 2020 |date=February 28, 2020}}</ref> Israeli singer [[Maya Bouskilla]] also announced that she was invited by [[Warner Music Group]] ([[Atlantic Records]]'s parent label) to record the song as a duet with Clarkson as part of a single release featuring select recording artists from all over the world,<ref name=\"Walla\">{{cite web |title=\u05e8\u05e9\u05de\u05d9\u05ea: \u05e7\u05dc\u05d9 \u05e7\u05dc\u05e8\u05e7\u05e1\u05d5\u05df \u05d4\u05e7\u05dc\u05d9\u05d8\u05d4 \u05d3\u05d5\u05d0\u05d8 \u05e2\u05dd \u05de\u05d0\u05d9\u05d4 \u05d1\u05d5\u05e1\u05e7\u05d9\u05dc\u05d4 \u05d1\u05e2\u05d1\u05e8\u05d9\u05ea |trans-title=Official: Kelly Clarkson recorded a duet with Maya Buskilla in Hebrew |language=Hebrew |url=https://e.walla.co.il/item/3346123 |first=Sagi |last=Ben-Nun |publisher=[[Walla!]] |accessdate=April 2, 2020 |date=March 12, 2020}}</ref> which included French singer [[Zaz (singer)|Zaz]], Canadian-Moroccan singer [[Faouzia]], Spanish singer [[Blas Cant\u00f3]], and German musical duo [[Glasperlenspiel (duo)|Glasperlenspiel]]. She also announced plans to film the single's debut live performance on ''[[The Kelly Clarkson Show]]'' on March 24, its original intended date of release, but was halted due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref name=\"Walla\" /> On April 3, 2020, Clarkson formally announced the single, which is set to be released on April 16, 2020, accompanied by a special episode of ''The Kelly Clarkson Show'' the same day.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kubota |first1=Samantha |title=Kelly Clarkson reveals new music coming later this month |url=https://www.today.com/popculture/kelly-clarkson-reveals-new-music-coming-later-month-t177505 |website=[[Today (American TV program)|The Today Show]] |publisher=[[NBCUniversal]] |accessdate=April 3, 2020 |date=April 3, 2020}}</ref> A 30-seconds snippet of the song has been posted on Clarkson's social media on April 14, 2020.\n\n== Track listing ==\n;Single \u2013 Multi-language Duets<ref name=\"Release - Multi-language Duets\">{{cite web |title=I Dare You (Multi-Language Duets) |url=https://open.spotify.com/album/4OUdmzLsYYpcUbCPS7TTZ7 |publisher=[[Spotify]] |date=April 16, 2020 |accessdate=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n{{Track listing\n| title1  = I Dare You\n| writer1 = \n{{Flatlist|\n* [[Jesse Shatkin]]\n* [[Jeff Gitelman]]\n* [[Natalie Hemby]]\n* Laura Veltz\n* [[Ben West (musician)|Ben West]]\n}}\n| length1 = 3:36\n\n| title2  = I Dare You (Appelle ton amour)\n| note2   = featuring [[Zaz (singer)|Zaz]]\n| writer2 = \n{{Flatlist|\n* [[:ko:Doriand|Doriand]]\n* [[Zaz (singer)|Isabelle Geffroy]]\n}}\n| length2 = 3:3